You have not experienced Meramec Caverns until you experience its magical appearance under the glow of a lantern. ZIPLINE The Caveman Zipline features a 90 minute canopy adventure. Three swinging sky-bridges, four zip rides varying in length from 200 to 1250 feet, and reaching speeds of 50 miles per hour makes this zipline a real thrill. Must be 10 years of age and must weigh at least 80 lbs., but no more than 270 lbs. For more information regarding the Caveman Zipline or to make reservations visit the Caveman Zipline Facebook page or visit their website at www.cavemanzipline.com. RIVERBOAT RIDES This half hour long tour on a canopy-topped riverboat is filled with gorgeous scenery of the Meramec River. While guests relax and enjoy the scenery the boat guide will enrich the tour by giving a rich history of the river and wildlife. The Cavern Queen I and Cavern Queen II run April through September giving guests a beautiful tour of the river. GIFT SHOP Meramec Caverns' gift shop is one of kind. Featuring traditional caverns memorabilia, to more exotic gifts guaranteed to wow you! Our gift shop carries a variety of quality and affordable souvenirs for the entire family. Our items include: rocks and minerals, apparel, jewelry, books, knives, clocks, pictures, postcards, toys, games, and more! GRANNY‚ÄôS Granny‚Äôs offers a variety of goodies! Granny‚Äôs makes fresh fudge in a wide variety of flavors including heath bar, peanut butter, mint chocolate chip, M&M, cinnamon crumb, vanilla, chocolate, and much more. Granny‚Äôs also offers a variety of candies, nuts, turtles, unique gifts, and other treats. Don‚Äôt miss out on the delights Granny‚Äôs has to offer! PANNING FOR GOLD Meramec Caverns' panning for gold is a gem of an activity for kids of all ages. Kids can pan for fool‚Äôs gold, fossils, and other gemstones while surrounded by a 19th century setting. A true treat for the summer months don‚Äôt let your kids miss this one of a kind activity! RESTAURANT Our restaurant features generous sized seating, up to 250 people including a private dining area. Our restaurant features home style cooking, a snack bar, and 28 flavors of ice-cream. On top of your regular dining experience we can cater for large groups such as family reunions, birthday parties, and company gatherings. FLOAT TRIPS Enjoy a six or eleven mile float trip down the scenic Meramec River. Canoes, kayaks, and rafts are available, weather permitting. After check-in at the Caverns' Camp Store, guests meet in the lower parking area where they will aboard a shuttle taking them up river where their float will launch. The end of the float brings guests back to Meramec Caverns where more fun awaits! For more information and reservations call (573) 468-6463 or visit https://www.americascave.com/river/#float CAMP GROUND Meramec Caverns' LaJolla Natural Park/Campgound holds a cache of scenic beauty and conveniences for visitors. Numerous trees shade the picnic area and river front campgrounds where trailer hookups, barbeque pits, sheltered pavilions, and a playground area are located. Showers, restrooms, and a concession stand are conveniently accessible to all. MOTEL The Meramec Caverns' Motel, located in LaJolla Natural Park, offers guests quiet and comfortable lodging.
